The paper discusses cognitive relaying in opportunistic spectrum access systems, which involves the use of sensing-based spectrum sharing and interference power constraint levels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Among these, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely as they directly relate to the communication and networking aspects of the paper, while cs.SY, cs.CR, and cs.AI are also relevant but to a lesser extent.
